# arc42 — {{project_name}}

Kompakte arc42-Instanz. C4-Diagramme sind als PlantUML eingebettet und durch ein normales PlantUML-Rendering (z. B. IntelliJ, VS Code PlantUML Plugin, kroki.io) darstellbar.

## 1. Einführung und Ziele

Modellgetriebene Fach-Applikation auf Quarkus. Ziel: aus deklarativen Modellen (PlantUML + MDA-Spec) eine konsistente, wartbare CRUD-/Prozess-Plattform ableiten.

**Qualitätsziele**

1. Korrektheit (keine Geschäftsregel im Adapter).
2. Testbarkeit (Testpyramide, ArchUnit, BDD).
3. Portabilität on-prem ↔ Cloud.

## 2. Randbedingungen

- JVM 21, Quarkus LTS.
- PostgreSQL 16 als Primärablage, H2 nur in Dev/Test.
- Keycloak (OIDC) für Auth.
- Schweizer Datenresidenz (VVG/FINMA).

## 3. Kontextabgrenzung

```plantuml
@startuml C4-L1
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Context.puml
Person(user, "Fachanwenderin")
System(mda, "{{project_name}}", "Modellgetriebene Fach-App")
System_Ext(kc, "Keycloak", "OIDC Provider")
System_Ext(db, "PostgreSQL", "Primärablage")
System_Ext(kafka, "Kafka", "Event Bus")
Rel(user, mda, "HTTPS/REST, OIDC-PKCE")
Rel(mda, kc, "OIDC")
Rel(mda, db, "JDBC, TLS")
Rel(mda, kafka, "Kafka (Avro)")
@enduml
```

## 4. Lösungsstrategie

- Hexagonale Architektur, DDD-taktisches Design.
- Transactional Outbox für Events.
- RLS + Tenant-Discriminator für Multi-Tenancy (Spec 5.4).

## 5. Bausteinsicht

### 5.1 C4-L2 Container

```plantuml
@startuml C4-L2
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Container.puml
System_Boundary(mda, "{{project_name}}") {
  Container(api, "Core API", "Quarkus (JVM 21)", "REST + OpenAPI")
  ContainerDb(db, "PostgreSQL", "16", "Entity Store, Audit")
}
Container_Ext(kc, "Keycloak", "OIDC")
Rel(api, kc, "Token Introspection")
Rel(api, db, "JDBC")
@enduml
```

### 5.2 C4-L3 Component (Bounded Context {{bc_name}})

```plantuml
@startuml C4-L3
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
Container_Boundary(api, "Core API") {
  Component(rest, "{{bc_name}}Resource", "JAX-RS", "HTTP-Adapter")
  Component(svc, "{{bc_name}}ApplicationService", "CDI + Transactional", "Use-Case-Orchestrierung")
  Component(dom, "{{bc_name}} Aggregate", "Pure Java", "Invarianten & Events")
  Component(repo, "{{bc_name}}PanacheRepository", "Panache", "Out-Port-Impl")
  ComponentDb(db, "{{bc_name}}", "Tabelle", "Aggregatdaten")
}
Rel(rest, svc, "ruft UseCase")
Rel(svc, dom, "nutzt")
Rel(svc, repo, "ruft Out-Port")
Rel(repo, db, "JPA/Panache")
@enduml
```

## 6. Laufzeitsicht (Beispiel: Register{{bc_name}})

```plantuml
@startuml
actor User
participant "{{bc_name}}Resource" as R
participant "{{bc_name}}ApplicationService" as S
participant "{{bc_name}} (Aggregate)" as A
participant "{{bc_name}}PanacheRepository" as P
participant "DomainEventPublisher" as E
User -> R: POST /api/v1/{{bc_path}}
R -> S: execute(RegisterCommand)
S -> A: register(...)
A --> S: aggregate + pendingEvents
S -> P: save(aggregate)
S -> E: publish(events)
S --> R: {{bc_name}}Id
R --> User: 201 Created + Location
@enduml
```

## 7. Verteilungssicht

- Quarkus-JAR + OCI-Image in AKS/Switzerland-North (Prod).
- Homelab: MicroK8s mit identischen Helm-Charts.

## 8. Querschnittliche Konzepte

- Auth: OIDC (Keycloak), Role-Claim via `groups`.
- Audit: Hibernate Envers + zusätzlicher fachlicher Audit-Log.
- Observability: OpenTelemetry → OTLP-Kollektor.

